{"word":"δεσπόσυνος","slug":"δεσπόσυνος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δεσπόσυνος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:δεσπότης'><el>δεσπότης</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>of</i> or <i>belonging to the master</i> or <i>lord</i>, <b>Hhymn.</b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>δ. ἀνάγκαι</el> <i>arbitrary</i> rule, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a> = <a href='S:δεσπότης'><el>δεσπότης</el></a>, <b>Tyrtae.</b><p/></div>"}]}